# Prism Demonstration Mode — Interactive Showcase Engine

A live, narrated demonstration system that puts Prism through its paces — showing self-control, browser control, and computer control capabilities with real actions, not simulations. Interruptible, resumable, and designed to **wow** anyone watching.

## Overview

The Demonstration Mode is a **guided tour** that executes real Prism capabilities in sequence, with a narration overlay explaining what's happening. It covers 9 demonstrations (3 per control surface) plus a full tab tour, all driven by a state machine that supports pause/resume/stop at any point.

