### Component Design

#### [NEW] `src/core/runtime/demonstration-engine.ts`

The server-side orchestrator. Manages demo state machine, executes demo steps, broadcasts progress via WebSocket.

```typescript
interface DemoState {
  status: "idle" | "running" | "paused" | "completed" | "error";
  currentDemo: string | null;
  currentStep: number;
  totalSteps: number;
  startedAt: string | null;
  pausedAt: string | null;
  completedDemos: string[];
  log: DemoLogEntry[];
}
```

- `startDemo()` — begins the full 9-demo + tab-tour sequence
- `pauseDemo()` / `resumeDemo()` — pauses mid-step, resumes from exact point
- `stopDemo()` — halts immediately, resets state
- `skipToDemo(demoId)` — jump to a specific demo
- Each step: executes action → emits narration event → waits delay → next

#### [NEW] `src/core/operator/public/demo-mode.js`

Client-side UI controller:
- Floating demo control bar (bottom of screen)
- Narration overlay panel with progress bar
- Tab switching via DOM manipulation
- WebSocket listener for server-pushed demo events
- Keyboard shortcuts: Space (pause/resume), Escape (stop)

#### [NEW] `src/core/operator/public/demo-mode.css`

Styles for the demo overlay, narration panel, progress bar, and control buttons.

#### [MODIFY] `src/core/operator/dashboard-service.ts`

New API routes:
- `POST /api/v1/demo/start` — start demo mode
- `POST /api/v1/demo/stop` — stop demo
- `POST /api/v1/demo/pause` — pause
- `POST /api/v1/demo/resume` — resume  
- `GET /api/v1/demo/status` — get current demo state

#### [MODIFY] `src/core/operator/public/dashboard-app.js`

- Import and initialize `demo-mode.js`
- Add "Demo Mode" button to sidebar
- Register keyboard shortcuts

